{
  "texts": [
    "Since clinical texts often do not correspond to the standards on which the available tokenizers have been trained, it is necessary to pay attention to this step as well.",
    "For example, it is common for dates or measurements to be pasted in (e.g., \"12nov,\" \"5 mL\").",
    "It is therefore very useful to systematically separate numbers and letters in the preprocessing.",
    "Expectedly, the rules have excellent precision but their recall is markedly insufficient.",
    "Hybridization, which consists in maximizing the recall by considering the entities predicted by at least one method, helps with a small number of annotated documents."
  ]
}